  "description": "The MIND DATA dataset comprises magnetoencephalography (MEG) recordings from the Weisend et al. (2007) study on cross-site pooling and standardization of MEG data. This dataset demonstrates the application of the MEG-BIDS format for organizing and sharing electrophysiological neuroimaging data, facilitating collaborative analysis and data harmonization across research institutions.",
